Ask HN: Moving to HFT as web/Java developer?
text:
Hello all,

I am currently a java backend developer and I have enjoyed by C/C++ projects on my own. My current job is very boring and has become mostly devops and writing forms. I want to get a job programming again and I was curious about this area.

Some notes:

1. What is HFT actually like? What do I program? I know usually they have math graduates do the models, do I spend most of my time programming those models?

2. How hard is the transition with just a cs minor? I never got a cs major and have considered a masters considering how bad the job market is.

Thanks!

Ask HN: WiFi smoke detector that doesn't require Internet access
text:
I'm looking for a smoke detector and CO2 sensor that I can connect to a private isolated Wi-Fi network. I want to be able to get the alerts and send to myself, but I really dislike connecting things to the Internet.

I find it hard to discover things like this because connected almost always means connected to a cloud server somewhere, with an app that polls that server.

Apologies if this question has been answered before, I've tried searching on here and on the greater internet but the ad copy is not very clear.

Thanks in advance!
